Tropical Cyclone Chido formed over the Southwestern Indian Ocean basin off the Madagascar coastline, is barreling towards Pemba on the Mozambique coastline and could affect parts of Malawi. The Southern Africa Development Cooperation Humanitarian and Emergency Operations Center earlier in the week issued an alert for the weather system.
